ta_service.py`\n  Line 118: **Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService; s = MetadataService(verbose=True); print(s.METADATA_FILES, s.verbose)\"` outputs correct values\n  Line 122: ## T10. MetadataService — load_metadata\n  Line 134: ## T11. MetadataService — save_metadata\n  Line 145: ## T12. MetadataService — update_metadata\n  Line 157: ## T13. MetadataService — validate_workspace\n  Line 164: from pathlib import Path; from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService\n  Line 165: s = MetadataService()\n  Line 175: ## T14. MetadataService — _validate_python_workspace\n  Line 187: ## T15. MetadataService — _validate_java_workspace\n  Line 200: - [ ] 16.2 Save to YAML via `MetadataService.save_metadata()`\n  Line 201: - [ ] 16.3 Load back via `MetadataService.load_metadata()`\n  Line 241: T9 (MetadataService skeleton)\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/design.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 — Design\n  Line 9: 3. **`MetadataService`** — service class providing `load_metadata()`, `save_metadata()`, `update_metadata()`, `validate_workspace()`, and language-specific workspace validation.\n  Line 11: These components form the foundation for all CLI lifecycle commands (`pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`) — each Runtime class reads/writes workspace metadata through `MetadataService` rather than direct file I/O.\n  Line 34: │  ├─ MetadataService │◄────────────│  asdict(opts)       │\n  Line 59: │   ├── __init__.py                        — __version__, exports (no MetadataService/AgentMetadata)\n  Line 68: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py                — PackRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n  Line 69: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py               — BuildRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n  Line 70: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py             — PublishRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n  Line 71: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py              — InvokeRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n  Line 72: │   │   └── status_runtime.py              — StatusRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n  Line 75: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py            — AgentMetadata + MetadataService (EXISTING)\n  Line 83:     │   ├── test_metadata_service.py       — MetadataService unit tests (EXISTING)\n  Line 252: ### 3.3 MetadataService (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n  Line 255: class MetadataService:\n  Line 394: **Note:** `MetadataService` validates presence of `pom.xml` but does not parse XML. `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility()` additionally parses `pom.xml` with `xml.etree.ElementTree` to verify well-formedness.\n  Line 414:   │     │     ├── MetadataService.load_metadata() → existing or None\n  Line 434:   │     │     └── MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n  Line 448:         ├── MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n  Line 457:         └── MetadataService.save_metadata() or update_metadata() (if state changes)\n  Line 512: - **`MetadataService`** does not wrap errors — it lets `yaml.YAMLError`, `ValidationError`, and `ValueError` propagate to callers.\n  Line 518: The `verbose` flag on `MetadataService` is stored but not actively used for logging in the current implementation. Future enhancement: add `logging.debug()` calls in `load_metadata`, `save_metadata`, and `update_metadata` when `self.verbose` is `True`.\n  Line 543: #### MetadataService Tests (`tests/services/test_metadata_service.py`)\n  Line 561: def service() -> MetadataService:\n  Line 562:     return MetadataService()\n  Line 604: - **MetadataService:** Real instance (lightweight, no external dependencies — only `yaml` and `pathlib`).\n  Line 634: 6. **`validate_workspace` naming**: Despite the name, `MetadataService.validate_workspace()` only checks for metadata file presence. Actual filesystem validation (`.py` files, `pom.xml`) is done by `_validate_python_workspace` and `_validate_java_workspace`, called from `PackRuntime._validate_language_compatibility()`.\n  Line 638: 8. **`services/__init__.py` exports**: Currently the file contains only a docstring. `MetadataService` and `AgentMetadata` are imported directly from `agentcube.services.metadata_service` by consumers (e.g., `PackRuntime`). No re-exports are added in this AR.\n  Line 646: 10. **Integration with existing Runtime classes**: All Runtime classes already import and use `MetadataService` and `AgentMetadata` from their canonical locations. No import path changes are needed — this AR documents and solidifies the existing implementation.\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md:\n  Line 3: AR: AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n  Line 30: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` |\n  Line 245: ## `MetadataService` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n  Line 248: class MetadataService:\n  Line 539: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-025: MetadataService 与数据模型 — Delta Spec\n  Line 119: ### Requirement: MetadataService.load_metadata\n  Line 125: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n  Line 130: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n  Line 135: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n  Line 140: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n  Line 145: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n  Line 150: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n  Line 154: - **GIVEN** `MetadataService(verbose=True)`\n  Line 160: ### Requirement: MetadataService.save_metadata\n  Line 166: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n  Line 171: - **WHEN** `Meta