{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861050234,"sessionID":"ses_2866ef6d6ffesXIQtY8ta7H3uE","part":{"id":"prt_d799127f3001U5K4dTB2ASDReS","messageID":"msg_d79911cb8001TnHoQZECMrzhHe","sessionID":"ses_2866ef6d6ffesXIQtY8ta7H3uE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2c1bb3f35e0643638921ce9f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** cmd/cli\n4: > **Language:** Python\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-025/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-025/design.md`, `changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md`\n8: > **Dependency:** None\n9: \n10: ## T1. AgentMetadata Pydantic Model — Field Definitions\n11: \n12: - [ ] 1.1 Define `AgentMetadata` as a Pydantic `BaseModel` in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n13: - [ ] 1.2 Add 2 required fields: `agent_name: str` (no default), `entrypoint: str` (no default)\n14: - [ ] 1.3 Add 3 validated fields with defaults: `language: str = \"python\"`, `port: int = 8080`, `build_mode: str = \"local\"`\n15: - [ ] 1.4 Add 4 string-default optional fields: `requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"`, `registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`, `registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"`, `registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n16: - [ ] 1.5 Add 13 `None`-default optional fields: `description`, `region`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`, `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`\n17: - [ ] 1.6 Add `Field(...)` descriptions for all 22 fields\n18: \n19: **Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata; m = AgentMetadata(agent_name='test', entrypoint='main.py'); print(len(m.model_fields))\"` outputs 22\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## T2. AgentMetadata — Language Validator\n24: \n25: - [ ] 2.1 Implement `@field_validator(\"language\", mode=\"before\")` that normalizes input to lowercase\n26: - [ ] 2.2 Accept `\"python\"` and `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n27: - [ ] 2.3 Return `\"python\"` as default when input is `None`\n28: - [ ] 2.4 Raise `ValueError` with message `\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'.\"` for unsupported values\n29: \n30: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidateLanguage -v` all pass\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## T3. AgentMetadata — Build Mode Validator\n35: \n36: - [ ] 3.1 Implement `@field_validator(\"build_mode\", mode=\"before\")` that normalizes input to lowercase\n37: - [ ] 3.2 Accept `\"local\"` and `\"cloud\"` (case-insensitive)\n38: - [ ] 3.3 Return `\"local\"` as default when input is `None`\n39: - [ ] 3.4 Raise `ValueError` with message `\"Unsupported build_mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'.\"` for unsupported values\n40: \n41: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidateBuildMode -v` all pass\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## T4. AgentMetadata — Port Validator\n46: \n47: - [ ] 4.1 Implement `@field_validator(\"port\")` (default mode, after type coercion)\n48: - [ ] 4.2 Accept ports in range `1..65535`\n49: - [ ] 4.3 Raise `ValueError` with message `\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\"` for out-of-range values\n50: \n51: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidatePort -v` all pass\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## T5. AgentMetadata — Serialization Tests\n56: \n57: - [ ] 5.1 Test `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` excludes all `None` fields\n58: - [ ] 5.2 Test required fields and defaults are present in dumped output\n59: - [ ] 5.3 Test minimal construction (required fields only) produces correct defaults\n60: - [ ] 5.4 Test full construction (all fields) preserves all values\n61: \n62: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidCreation -v` and `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataModelDump -v` all pass\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ## T6. MetadataOptions Dataclass — Field Definitions\n67: \n68: - [ ] 6.1 Define `MetadataOptions` as a `@dataclass` in `agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n69: - [ ] 6.2 Add 14 optional fields with correct defaults:\n70:   - `agent_name: Optional[str] = None`\n71:   - `language: Optional[str] = \"python\"`\n72:   - `entrypoint: Optional[str] = None`\n73:   - `port: Optional[int] = 8080`\n74:   - `build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"`\n75:   - `requirements_file: Optional[str] = None`\n76:   - `description: Optional[str] = None`\n77:   - `workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n78:   - `router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n79:   - `readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n80:   - `readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080`\n81:   - `registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n82:   - `registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n83:   - `registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n84:   - `agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n85: \n86: **Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions; o = MetadataOptions(); print(len(o.__dataclass_fields__))\"` outputs 15\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## T7. MetadataOptions — from_options Classmethod\n91: \n92: - [ ] 7.1 Implement `from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any])` classmethod\n93: - [ ] 7.2 Define `known_fields` set with all 15 field names\n94: - [ ] 7.3 Filter input dict to only known fields (silently ignore unknown keys)\n95: - [ ] 7.4 Return `cls(**filtered)` instance\n96: \n97: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py::TestMetadataOptionsFromOptions -v` all pass\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ## T8. MetadataOptions — Default Values Tests\n102: \n103: - [ ] 8.1 Test all 15 fields have expected default values when constructed with no arguments\n104: - [ ] 8.2 Test `from_options({})` returns instance with all defaults\n105: - [ ] 8.3 Test `from_options` with partial dict sets only specified fields\n106: - [ ] 8.4 Test `from_options` with unknown keys ignores them\n107: \n108: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py -v` all pass\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## T9. MetadataService — Class Skeleton and Constants\n113: \n114: - [ ] 9.1 Define `MetadataService` class in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n115: - [ ] 9.2 Add class constant `METADATA_FILES: List[str] = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]`\n116: - [ ] 9.3 Add `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)` storing `self.verbose`\n117: \n118: **Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService; s = MetadataService(verbose=True); print(s.METADATA_FILES, s.verbose)\"` outputs correct values\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## T10. MetadataService — load_metadata\n123: \n124: - [ ] 10.1 Implement `load_metadata(workspace_path: Path) -> Optional[AgentMetadata]`\n125: - [ ] 10.2 Iterate through `METADATA_FILES` in priority order\n126: - [ ] 10.3 For first existing file: open, `yaml.safe_load()`, handle `None` result as `{}`, return `AgentMetadata(**data)`\n127: - [ ] 10.4 Return `None` if no metadata file exists\n128: - [ ] 10.5 Do not catch `yaml.YAMLError` or `ValidationError` — let them propagate\n129: \n130: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestLoadMetadataPrimaryExists -v`, `::TestLoadMetadataFirstFallback -v`, `::TestLoadMetadataSecondFallback -v`, `::TestLoadMetadataNoneExist -v` all pass\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ## T11. MetadataService — save_metadata\n135: \n136: - [ ] 11.1 Implement `save_metadata(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n137: - [ ] 11.2 Always write to `agent_metadata.yaml` (canonical filename)\n138: - [ ] 11.3 Use `metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)` for data\n139: - [ ] 11.4 Call `yaml.dump(data, f, default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)`\n140: \n141: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestSaveMetadataRoundTrip -v`, `::TestSaveMetadataExcludeNone -v`, `::TestSaveMetadataFormat -v` all pass\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ## T12. MetadataService — update_metadata\n146: \n147: - [ ] 12.1 Implement `update_metadata(workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata`\n148: - [ ] 12.2 Call `load_metadata()` — if `None`, create default `AgentMetadata` using `updates` for required fields and `workspace_path.name` fallback for `agent_name`\n149: - [ ] 12.3 Call `existing.model_copy(update=updates)` for immutable merge with re-validation\n150: - [ ] 12.4 Call `save_metadata()` with merged result\n151: - [ ] 12.5 Return merged `AgentMetadata` instance\n152: \n153: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestUpdateMetadataMerge -v`, `::TestUpdateMetadataCreateNew -v` all pass\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## T13. MetadataService — validate_workspace\n158: \n159: - [ ] 13.1 Implement `validate_workspace(workspace_path: Path) -> bool`\n160: - [ ] 13.2 Return `self.load_metadata(workspace_path) is not None`\n161: - [ ] 13.3 Note: This checks metadata file presence only, not filesystem structure\n162: \n163: **Verification:** `python -c \"\n164: from pathlib import Path; from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService\n165: s = MetadataService()\n166: import tempfile; ws = Path(tempfile.mkdtemp())\n167: (ws / 'agent_metadata.yaml').write_text('agent_name: t\\nentrypoint: m\\n')\n168: print(s.validate_workspace(ws))  # True\n169: (ws / 'agent_metadata.yaml').unlink()\n170: print(s.validate_workspace(ws))  # False\n171: \"`\n172: \n173: ---\n174: \n175: ## T14. MetadataService — _validate_python_workspace\n176: \n177: - [ ] 14.1 Implement `_validate_python_workspace(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n178: - [ ] 14.2 Check at least one `*.py` file exists in workspace root via `workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\")`\n179: - [ ] 14.3 Raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` if no `.py` files\n180: - [ ] 14.4 Check requirements file exists (use `metadata.requirements_file` or default `\"requirements.txt\"`)\n181: - [ ] 14.5 Raise `ValueError(f\"Dependency file not found: {req_file}\")` if missing\n182: \n183: **Verification:** Manual test with workspace containing/missing `.py` and `requirements.txt` files\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## T15. MetadataService — _validate_java_workspace\n188: \n189: - [ ] 15.1 Implement `_validate_java_workspace(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n190: - [ ] 15.2 Check `pom.xml` exists in workspace root\n191: - [ ] 15.3 Raise `ValueError(\"pom.xml is required for Java projects\")` if missing\n192: \n193: **Verification:** Manual test with workspace containing/missing `pom.xml`\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ## T16. Round-trip Consistency Test\n198: \n199: - [ ] 16.1 Create `AgentMetadata` with mix of required, default, and optional fields\n200: - [ ] 16.2 Save to YAML via `MetadataService.save_metadata()`\n201: - [ ] 16.3 Load back via `MetadataService.load_metadata()`\n202: - [ ] 16.4 Verify all non-None field values match original\n203: \n204: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestSaveMetadataRoundTrip -v` passes\n205: \n206: ---\n207: \n208: ## T17. Error Handling Verification\n209: \n210: - [ ] 17.1 Verify malformed YAML raises `yaml.YAMLError`\n211: - [ ] 17.2 Verify unsupported language in YAML raises `ValidationError`\n212: - [ ] 17.3 Verify missing required field raises `ValidationError`\n213: - [ ] 17.4 Verify port out of range in update raises `ValidationError` and does not modify file\n214: \n215: **Verification:** All covered by existing test classes `TestAgentMetadataValidateLanguage`, `TestAgentMetadataValidateBuildMode`, `TestAgentMetadataValidatePort`\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## T18. Linting and Type Checking\n220: \n221: - [ ] 18.1 Run `ruff check` on `metadata_service.py` and `pack_models.py` — no violations\n222: - [ ] 18.2 Run `mypy` on `metadata_service.py` and `pack_models.py` — no type errors\n223: \n224: **Verification:** `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` and `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` both pass\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Task Dependencies\n229: \n230: ```\n231: T1 (AgentMetadata fields)\n232: ├── T2 (language validator)\n233: ├── T3 (build_mode validator)\n234: ├── T4 (port validator)\n235: └── T5 (serialization tests)\n236: \n237: T6 (MetadataOptions fields)\n238: └── T7 (from_options)\n239:     └── T8 (defaults tests)\n240: \n241: T9 (MetadataService skeleton)\n242: ├── T10 (load_metadata)\n243: ├── T11 (save_metadata)\n244: ├── T12 (update_metadata)\n245: ├── T13 (validate_workspace)\n246: ├── T14 (_validate_python_workspace)\n247: └── T15 (_validate_java_workspace)\n248: \n249: T10, T11, T12\n250: └── T16 (round-trip test)\n251: \n252: T2, T3, T4, T10, T12\n253: └── T17 (error handling)\n254: \n255: T1-T17\n256: └── T18 (linting + type check)\n257: ```\n258: \n259: ## Parallelizable Groups\n260: \n261: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n262: |-------|-------|---------------|\n263: | G1 | T1, T6, T9 | None |\n264: | G2 | T2, T3, T4 | T1 |\n265: | G3 | T7 | T6 |\n266: | G4 | T10, T11, T13, T14, T15 | T9 |\n267: | G5 | T5, T8 | T2, T3, T4, T7 |\n268: | G6 | T12 | T10, T11 |\n269: | G7 | T16, T17 | T10, T11, T12, T2, T3, T4 |\n270: | G8 | T18 | T1-T17 |\n271: \n272: ---\n273: \n274: ## Acceptance Criteria\n275: \n276: | # | Criterion | Command |\n277: |---|-----------|---------|\n278: | AC1 | AgentMetadata has 22 fields with correct types and defaults | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidCreation -v` |\n279: | AC2 | Language validator accepts python/java, rejects others | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidateLanguage -v` |\n280: | AC3 | Build mode validator accepts local/cloud, rejects others | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidateBuildMode -v` |\n281: | AC4 | Port validator accepts 1-65535, rejects out of range | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidatePort -v` |\n282: | AC5 | model_dump(exclude_none=True) works correctly | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataModelDump -v` |\n283: | AC6 | MetadataOptions has 15 fields with correct defaults | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py::TestMetadataOptionsDefaults -v` |\n284: | AC7 | from_options filters known fields, ignores unknown | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py::TestMetadataOptionsFromOptions -v` |\n285: | AC8 | load_metadata tries primary → fallback1 → fallback2 → None | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py -k LoadMetadata -v` |\n286: | AC9 | save_metadata writes clean YAML with correct formatting | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py -k SaveMetadata -v` |\n287: | AC10 | update_metadata merges and validates correctly | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py -k UpdateMetadata -v` |\n288: | AC11 | validate_workspace returns boolean based on metadata presence | Manual verification |\n289: | AC12 | _validate_python_workspace checks .py and requirements file | Manual verification |\n290: | AC13 | _validate_java_workspace checks pom.xml | Manual verification |\n291: | AC14 | Round-trip save → load produces equivalent values | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestSaveMetadataRoundTrip -v` |\n292: | AC15 | All tests pass | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py -v` |\n293: | AC16 | No linting violations | `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` |\n294: | AC17 | No type errors | `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` |\n\n(End of file - total 294 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** cmd/cli\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-025/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-025/design.md`, `changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** None\n\n## T1. AgentMetadata Pydantic Model — Field Definitions\n\n- [ ] 1.1 Define `AgentMetadata` as a Pydantic `BaseModel` in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- [ ] 1.2 Add 2 required fields: `agent_name: str` (no default), `entrypoint: str` (no default)\n- [ ] 1.3 Add 3 validated fields with defaults: `language: str = \"python\"`, `port: int = 8080`, `build_mode: str = \"local\"`\n- [ ] 1.4 Add 4 string-default optional fields: `requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"`, `registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`, `registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"`, `registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n- [ ] 1.5 Add 13 `None`-default optional fields: `description`, `region`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`, `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`\n- [ ] 1.6 Add `Field(...)` descriptions for all 22 fields\n\n**Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata; m = AgentMetadata(agent_name='test', entrypoint='main.py'); print(len(m.model_fields))\"` outputs 22\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T07